# Annotation Property: pbpko:IAO_0000111 (editor preferred term)

AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000111 pbpko:IAO_0000111 "editor preferred term"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000114 pbpko:IAO_0000111 pbpko:IAO_0000122)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000115 pbpko:IAO_0000111 "The concise, meaningful, and human-friendly name for a class or property preferred by the ontology developers. (US-English)"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000117 pbpko:IAO_0000111 "PERSON:Daniel Schober"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000119 pbpko:IAO_0000111 "GROUP:OBI:<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/obi>"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pbpko:IAO_0000111 "editor preferred term"@en)

# Annotation Property: pbpko:IAO_0000112 (example of usage)

AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000111 pbpko:IAO_0000112 "example of usage"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000114 pbpko:IAO_0000112 pbpko:IAO_0000122)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000115 pbpko:IAO_0000112 "A phrase describing how a term should be used and/or a citation to a work which uses it. May also include other kinds of examples that facilitate immediate understanding, such as widely know prototypes or instances of a class, or cases where a relation is said to hold."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000117 pbpko:IAO_0000112 "PERSON:Daniel Schober"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000119 pbpko:IAO_0000112 "GROUP:OBI:<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/obi>"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pbpko:IAO_0000112 "example of usage"@en)

# Annotation Property: pbpko:IAO_0000114 (has curation status)

AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000111 pbpko:IAO_0000114 "has curation status"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000117 pbpko:IAO_0000114 "PERSON:Alan Ruttenberg"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000117 pbpko:IAO_0000114 "PERSON:Bill Bug"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000117 pbpko:IAO_0000114 "PERSON:Melanie Courtot"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pbpko:IAO_0000114 "has curation status"@en)

# Annotation Property: pbpko:IAO_0000115 (definition)

AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000111 pbpko:IAO_0000115 "definition"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000114 pbpko:IAO_0000115 pbpko:IAO_0000122)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000115 pbpko:IAO_0000115 "The official definition, explaining the meaning of a class or property. Shall be Aristotelian, formalized and normalized. Can be augmented with colloquial definitions."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000116 pbpko:IAO_0000115 "2012-04-05: 
Barry Smith

The official OBI definition, explaining the meaning of a class or property: 'Shall be Aristotelian, formalized and normalized. Can be augmented with colloquial definitions'  is terrible.

Can you fix to something like:

A statement of necessary and sufficient conditions explaining the meaning of an expression referring to a class or property.

Alan Ruttenberg

Your proposed definition is a reasonable candidate, except that it is very common that necessary and sufficient conditions are not given. Mostly they are necessary, occasionally they are necessary and sufficient or just sufficient. Often they use terms that are not themselves defined and so they effectively can't be evaluated by those criteria. 

On the specifics of the proposed definition:

We don't have definitions of 'meaning' or 'expression' or 'property'. For 'reference' in the intended sense I think we use the term 'denotation'. For 'expression', I think we you mean symbol, or identifier. For 'meaning' it differs for class and property. For class we want documentation that let's the intended reader determine whether an entity is instance of the class, or not. For property we want documentation that let's the intended reader determine, given a pair of potential relata, whether the assertion that the relation holds is true. The 'intended reader' part suggests that we also specify who, we expect, would be able to understand the definition, and also generalizes over human and computer reader to include textual and logical definition. 

Personally, I am more comfortable weakening definition to documentation, with instructions as to what is desirable. 

We also have the outstanding issue of how to aim different definitions to different audiences. A clinical audience reading chebi wants a different sort of definition documentation/definition from a chemistry trained audience, and similarly there is a need for a definition that is adequate for an ontologist to work with."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000117 pbpko:IAO_0000115 "PERSON:Daniel Schober"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000119 pbpko:IAO_0000115 "GROUP:OBI:<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/obi>"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pbpko:IAO_0000115 "definition"@en)

# Annotation Property: pbpko:IAO_0000116 (editor note)

AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000111 pbpko:IAO_0000116 "editor note"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000114 pbpko:IAO_0000116 pbpko:IAO_0000122)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000115 pbpko:IAO_0000116 "An administrative note intended for its editor. It may not be included in the publication version of the ontology, so it should contain nothing necessary for end users to understand the ontology."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000117 pbpko:IAO_0000116 "PERSON:Daniel Schober"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000119 pbpko:IAO_0000116 "GROUP:OBI:<http://purl.obofoundry.org/obo/obi>"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pbpko:IAO_0000116 "editor note"@en)

# Annotation Property: pbpko:IAO_0000117 (term editor)

AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000111 pbpko:IAO_0000117 "term editor"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000114 pbpko:IAO_0000117 pbpko:IAO_0000122)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000115 pbpko:IAO_0000117 "Name of editor entering the term in the file. The term editor is a point of contact for information regarding the term. The term editor may be, but is not always, the author of the definition, which may have been worked upon by several people"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000116 pbpko:IAO_0000117 "20110707, MC: label update to term editor and definition modified accordingly. See https://github.com/information-artifact-ontology/IAO/issues/115."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000117 pbpko:IAO_0000117 "PERSON:Daniel Schober"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000119 pbpko:IAO_0000117 "GROUP:OBI:<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/obi>"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pbpko:IAO_0000117 "term editor"@en)

# Annotation Property: pbpko:IAO_0000118 (alternative label)

AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000111 pbpko:IAO_0000118 "alternative label"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000114 pbpko:IAO_0000118 pbpko:IAO_0000125)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000115 pbpko:IAO_0000118 "A label for a class or property that can be used to refer to the class or property instead of the preferred rdfs:label. Alternative labels should be used to indicate community- or context-specific labels, abbreviations, shorthand forms and the like."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000117 pbpko:IAO_0000118 "OBO Operations committee")
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000117 pbpko:IAO_0000118 "PERSON:Daniel Schober"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(pbpko:IAO_0000119 pbpko:IAO_0000118 "GROUP:OBI:<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/obi>"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pbpko:IAO_0000118 "alternative label"@en)

